Description: MeGlobe is a web-based instant messaging platform that provides free messaging and real-time language translation.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: MeGlobe is a free web based instant messenger that has incorporated real-time language translation technology into its service. While it is true that Machine Translation (MT) has come a long way since its first public demo in 1954; it still lacks the ability to account for the ambiguity, syntactic irregularity, multiple word meanings and the contextual influences that arise within natural conversations. We've, implemented a novel, community based solution into our translation engine to address these problems. Whenever MeGlobe provides a translation that is incorrect, users have the ability to contribute and make edits to the translations themselves. These contributions are used to improve translation accuracy and quality. Every contribution made by the community allows MeGlobe to better account for colloquialisms, multiple word meanings, contextual influence or anything else that arises during natural conversations or the use of natural language patterns. This approach effectively introduces a human element to machine translation without sacrificing speed and autonomy and brings us one step closer to our dream of unifying the global online community. MeGlobe also provides access to AIM, Yahoo and MSN chat networks.
Industry Groups: Information Technology, Internet Services, Messaging and Telecommunications, Sales and Marketing

Description: Open Television Network provides web service that enables audio and video content.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: The Open Television Network provides a web service called klickTab that enables audio and video content owners to sell their content within an RSS feed inside standard 'podcast' aggregators. The klickTab system is an unmediated marketplace open to any content owner who wants to sell in a non-discriminatory manner. Each merchant creates their own account and hosts their own content. They enter metadata on content items within the klickTab system and can sell individual items in an RSS feed (that sends the media item to their aggregator of choice) or they can create channel feeds analogous to standard podcasts. Merchants get embed codes for the single item sale, or for the channel feeds they create. We provide a template for easily creating a store within the merchant's site in addition to the embed code for item and feeds. The OpenTVNetwork.com site is used to showcase content available in the system. Content can be purchased there, and feeds subscribed to. Open Television Network takes 15% of the price the merchant sets for their content. Affiliates (when available) will get 15% from the merchant's share, unless the merchant opts out of affiliate sales.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment, Video

Description: KnoFolio is an art and design portfolio-building platform that offers online courses, critiques, and connections to top art colleges.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: KnoFolio is an art & design portfolio-building platform that offers online courses, critique, and connection to the top art colleges. Description: KnoFolio empowers aspiring artists to create a digital portfolio and share it with prestigious art & design colleges across the United States. KnoFolio offers portfolio development courses, constructive critique, and connection to the top art colleges in North America. Rationale: There are no meaningful online art college preparatory platforms despite a stated need from admission counselors and students. There are many websites that help students fulfill admissions criteria for traditional colleges and universities. The platforms usually take the form of ACT/SAT E-learning. The ACT/SAT is the key differentiator in a student’s application for traditional colleges and universities, whereas the portfolio is the key differentiator in a student’s application for an art college. KnoFolio will fill the demand for online portfolio development. It will be in a digital environment to free the student from the constraints of time and space. Students will have the ability to create a portfolio that meets the standards of art colleges without being hindered by economic or geographic constraints. Components: KnoFolio is broken into 4 components. These components reflect the essentials of a pre-college art program, and will provide the criteria to develop a meaningful body of work. •Portfolio Users will have the ability to upload their work, categorize it, and get it in front of The KnoFolio Community. •Critique The KnoFolio Community will provide meaningful critique on submitted work. •Development Courses Users will be offered many portfolio development courses that will help students create meaningful work that reflects what art colleges desire. •Art College Match Users will be able to browse accredited art & design colleges to find the best match for their artistic pursuits.
Industry Groups: Education, Financial Services, Media and Entertainment, Sales and Marketing

Headquarters Regions: Greater Los Angeles Area, Inland Empire, West Coast
Full Description: Drywall Dreams is a drywall and insulation company that offers a wide range of services to help improve the energy efficiency and aesthetic appeal of homes and commercial properties. Their team has years of experience and is committed to delivering workmanship and customer service. One of the services they offer is drywall installation. Whether you are building a new home or renovating an existing one, their team can install drywall to give your walls a smooth and seamless finish. They also offer drywall repair services, which can restore your walls to their original condition after they have been damaged. In addition to drywall services, they also provide a variety of insulation services. Proper insulation is crucial for maintaining a comfortable indoor environment and reducing energy costs. They offer blown-in insulation, fiberglass insulation, and spray foam insulation, which can help improve the energy efficiency of your property. Blown-in insulation involves blowing insulation material into your walls or attic, while fiberglass insulation involves installing batts or rolls of insulation. Spray foam insulation is a type of insulation that is sprayed onto surfaces and then expands to fill gaps and cracks. Their team works closely with clients to determine which type of insulation is best suited for their property and budget. They also offer insulation removal services, which can remove old or damaged insulation and prepare your property for new insulation.

Description: Online collaboration software that provides a central place for teams to easily organize and track things worth tracking
Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: We’re a small team of designers, developers, marketers and project managers from across the globe. We’re not software industry veterans, productivity experts, or management gurus; we’re just a group of young, hardworking do-ers with a passion for pushing our creative boundaries and elevating simplicity to its highest form.  We built Trackolade because we wanted to eliminate the costs of complexity that pervade ordinary project management software. We believe that simplicity is beautiful, that elegance trumps endless extras, and that ease-of-use is a measure of success. We looked long and hard at what features are really necessary and truly enhance productivity in a project management tool, and then we built that - and only that - into Trackolade. We think that flexibility and control are more valuable than having a stack of features, so we designed Trackolade to work the way effective teams work naturally - by making to-do lists, prioritizing through consensus, and collaborating constantly. We knew we were onto something when we started using Trackolade ourselves and our productivity, communication, and efficiency shot through the roof.  We decided to share Trackolade with the world because we know we’re not the only group of people working together towards a common goal who have experienced disorder, confusion and anarchy. We don’t have investors, we’re not huge risk takers, and we weren't incubated anywhere (unless you count our homemade office). We are simply a group of creators who want to produce the best work we can and have fun doing it - just like you. We hope our story inspires you, and moreover, that Trackolade empowers you.
